to face in the presence of imagination.  Here, it denotes the comprehensive way-station of basmala, which has 19 letters.  The treatise ends with an account of the mystical ascent (mirʿāj). See FM I:171-180.  </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>OY lists 10 mss., with one very good historic ms. verifying the work: the holograph Veliyuddin 1759 (618H) with a samāʿ written by Ibn Sawakīn in Aleppo. It also appears in other good collections, particularly Beyazid 3750 and Carullah 986. OY dates the composition to 603H based on a note at the end of Beyazit 3750 (432a), but we could not verify this; it is possible that there is some confusion with a note on another work. </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>99</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>106</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Futuhat Chapter 22</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="55" RECORDID="45"><COL><DATA>414</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>45</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>K. Maqām al-qurba</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>كتاب مقام القربة</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Verified A.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Maqam al qurba</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>IA</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>al-ḥamdu lillāh mukhṣiṣ man shāʾa min ʿibādihi </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>OY: Treatise on the Divine Proximity and the ways of entering it.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>A much copied work, verified by two good historic ms. The best is Veliyuddin 1759 (holograph with samāʿ dated 617H in Aleppo and 633H in Damascus).Also KÖPRÜLÜ Fazıl Ahmed Pş 53, ff. 152-155</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>II, 24-25, 260-262.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="30" RECORDID="48"><COL><DATA>421</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>48</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>K. Marātib al-taqwā</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>كتاب مراتب التقوى</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Unverified.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Maratib</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA