but as we have not yet obtained a digital copy, cannot compare the two mss.JC notes discrepancy between the text and the added red numbers from ch. 4 onwards: from chapter “five” to chapter “sixteen” the red ink number (467-478) is one less than the corresponding FM chapter number (ch.468-479); from chapter “seventeen” to “sixty” the red ink number (479-522) is four less than the corresponding FM chapter number (ch.483-526); from chapter “sixty-one” to “ninety-one” (the last in the ms) there are no red ink numbers – and these correspond to FM ch.527-557. In summary, the text of RG 35 K. al-Aqṭāb has the appearance of a highly abbreviated version of FM ch.462-557, omitting ch.480-482 entirely. It is possible that RG 35 is an early form or summary of sifr 17 of the first recension text of FM.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>4/74-195 as Aqṭāb al-Muḥammadiyya wa manāzilihim.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="30" RECORDID="422"><COL><DATA>38</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>422</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>K. al-Arbaʿīn ḥadīthan</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>كتاب الأربعين حديثا</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Not IA.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>arba</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Ṣadr al-Dīn al-Qūnawī (d.673)</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>A commentary on 40 ḥadīth, but only completed up to the 29th.  </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Only one ms. in Izmirli 3690/ 9, dated 1333: OY classifies it as a copy of IA’s K. al-Arbaʿīn ḥadīthan fī al-ṭiwālāt. According to Stephen Hirtenstein, it is actually a copy of SQ’s Sharḥ al-Arbaʿīn ḥadīth. </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>31</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>32</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="14" RECORDID="425"><COL><DATA>41.1</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>425</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>R. fī al-Arwāḥ</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>رسالة في الأرواح</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Unverified.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>arwah</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Treatise on the angelic spirits and their different categories.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Only one ms, Zahiriye 5433/241b-242b.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>133</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>143</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>9. 267, 268, 351</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="20" RECORDID="426"><COL><DATA>43</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>135</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>426</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>K. al-Asmāʾ</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>كتاب الأسماء</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>No mss.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>asma</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>No surviving mss., reported in both the lists which IA made of his own works, Fihris muʾallafāt al-shaykh al-akbar (RG 142) and Ijāza li-l-malik al-Muẓaffar (RG 269).</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>161</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>172</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="25" RECORDID="428"><COL><DATA>45</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>313</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>428</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>K. al-Asrār</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>كتاب الأسرار</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>OY duplicate.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Asrar</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Only two mss. listed by OY, Shehit Ali  1314 and Haci Mahmud 2540. Shehit Ali has been checked and found to be K. al-Isrā (RG 313); OY has it down under both numbers, so we have regarded this as a duplicate. According to OY, Haci Mahmud 2540 is a Turkish translation by Ibrahim b. Muhammad of an unidentified treatise by IA in 24 chapters, but we have not yet had the chance to inspect it.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>278</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></C