ح مشاهد الأسرار</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Commentary</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Sitt al-ʿAjam</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>al-ḥamdu lillāh al-awwal qabl al-akwān al-maʾlūfiyya</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Commentary by Sitt al-ʿAjam (d. c. 1288) on Mashāhid al-asrār; an original dated 686/1287, (in the hand of her scribe as she was illiterate). </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Ayasofia 2019 is probably the original text, written by a relative of Sitt al-ʿAjam as she herself was illiterate. Used by Beneito and Hakim in producing the critical edition of Mashāhid, and now published by Hakim and Aladdin as a critical edition (Institut Francais, Damascus) </DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="17" RECORDID="632"><COL><DATA>333</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>632</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Kashf al-ḍamīr min aḥruf al-taksīr</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>كشف الضمير من أحرف التكسير</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Unverified.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Kashf</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>A treatise on letters.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Only one ms, Hekimoglu 530, mentioned in OY and we have not found any more during our research. According to OY, there is a commentary upon the text   Bayān al-manzūm al-maktūm by Shaykh Ibn al-Yamanī also in the same ms. </DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="26" RECORDID="633"><COL><DATA>647</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>543</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>633</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Sayr al-hilāl</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>سير الهلال</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Unverified.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Sayr</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></C