of his metaphysics; the Divine Essence and Attributes, the human being as the intermediary between Creator and Creation, and the author’s conception of the Universal Reality (al-haqīqa al-kulliya). Built around a pronounced philosophical framework, almost in the kalām style, and copiously illustrated with diagrams and tables. (Fenton and Gloton).</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>A much copied work, verified by two historic mss.: Manisa 1183 (655H taken from al-Ḥabashī’s copy), and Veliyuddin 1686 (c.667 and copied by disciple of SQ’s). We know from its mention in al-Tadbīrāt al-Ilāhīya (see Elmore JMIAS 29) that this was one of the first works IA began, but the surviving versions are later, probably written in Tunis in 598/1202 at the home of al-Mahdawī (see FM. Chapter 4).</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="26" RECORDID="639"><COL><DATA>552</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>639</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>al-Nuṣūṣ</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>النصوص</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Not IA.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Ṣadr al-Dīn al-Qūnawī (d. 673)</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>al- ḥamdu lillāhi alladhi abāna bi-mustaqarrāt al-himam marātib ‘ilm al-yaqīn</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>A well-known work by SQ.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>OY has given this an RG number and listed three mss. However, all the mss that we have  looked at are the well-known work by SQ. </DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="9" RECORDID="640"><COL><DATA>568</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>102.2</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>640</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Qaṣīda fī al-kīmiyāʾ</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>قصيدة في الكيمياء</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>OY duplicate.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Qasida</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA>